The SA soldier killed in a “friendly fire” incident while on a peacekeeping mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo has been named as Private Simanga Arthur Khuselo. The 37-year-old is survived by his wife and two children. SA National Defence Force (SANDF) spokesperson Brig-Gen Mafi Mgobozi said the 37-year-old was stationed at Unit 1 Tactical Intelligence Regiment in Potchefstroom. The army announced on Thursday that Khuselo died after succumbing to his injuries following an  incident during a military operation in Kilia, on the eastern outskirts of the DRC. Mgobozi said details of the incident were sketchy and  a board of inquiry has been convened to investigate. Mgobozi said funeral arrangements will be announced as soon as the family had finalised the details. TimesLIVE